-- Man Arrested After 13 Injured in Stabbing Attack in Japan, Yomiuri Reports
-- B y   S t e v e n   M c P h e r s o n
-- 2010-12-17T00:37:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/man-arrested-after-13-injured-in-stabbing-attack-in-japan-yomiuri-reports.html
Thirteen people were hurt in a knife
attack in a bus near a train station in Ibaraki prefecture,
Japan, the Yomiuri newspaper reported. A 27-year-old man is in
custody, according to the report, which cited local police. Four
junior high school students and seven high school students were
among the injured, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven McPherson at 
 smcpherson@bloomberg.net  